article.headline: Texas Tech 75, Oklahoma State 49
article.story:
LUBBOCK, Texas (AP) -- Alesha Robertson scored a game-high 18
points and freshman Raquel Christian added 13 points off the bench
to lead Texas Tech over Oklahoma State 75-49 Saturday night.

Tech (10-6, 1-1 Big 12), up 15 at halftime, allowed the Cowgirls
to cut the deficit to 37-30 three minutes into the second half. But
from that point the Lady Raiders, powered by 10 points from
Christian and nine from Chesley Dabbs, outscored Oklahoma State
38-19 to close out the game.

The Lady Raiders scored 22 points off turnovers.

Tech shot 9 of 17 from beyond the 3-point arc, with seven of
those coming from Robertson and Christian.

Oklahoma State (12-2, 1-1) had its four-game winning streak
snapped. Andrea Riley finished with a team-high 14 points for the
Cowgirls, and Rashidat Sadiq added 12.

Robertson scored 14 of her 18 points in the first half while
Dabbs finished with 11.
